This paper focuses on training a deep convolutional neural network for face attribute classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the optimal sharing pattern of computational resources within the network, which involves determining the best way to allocate resources for efficient computation, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with emotion classification, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM), and the dataset used for training includes ethnicity labels, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
